Cooper Industries Inc asked theFederal Trade Commission to vacate a 1979 order that requiresthe company to get FTC approval before making certainacquisitions, the FTC said.    The order was issued as part of a settlement of FTC chargesthat Cooper's merger with Gardner-Denver Co would lessencompetion and increase concentration in the gas compressor andindustrial air tool industries, the FTC said.    The order requires that, until 1989, Cooper must get FTCapproval before acquiring companies in the natural gascompressor or hand-held industrial pneumatic tool businesses. Reuter&#3;